    <h4>Our program of study has been carefully designed to give you the skills you will need to be successful in the creative workplace. Your studies will have a dual focus that will enable you to explore and understand the Creative Industries as both creative process and commercial activity.</h4> 
<h4>&nbsp;</h4> 
<h4>Creative Industries students have access to courses in all of&nbsp;The&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/fcad/">Faculty of Communication Design</a>&nbsp;sister schools:</h4> 
<h4>- The School of Fashion</h4> 
<h4>- Graphic Communications Management</h4> 
<h4>- Radio and Television Arts</h4> 
<h4>- Image Arts</h4> 
<h4>- Journalism</h4> 
<h4>- Professional Communications</h4> 
<h4>- Theatre and Performance</h4> 
<h4>- Interior Design</h4> 
<h4>&nbsp;</h4> 
<h4>They also undertake a business concentration delivered by the Ted Rogers School of Management – Canada’s largest undergraduate business school.</h4>
    





